  [Text] <PERSON>Ivo Hlavacek</PERSON>, the director of the section for 
international law and consular affairs of the <ORGANIZATION>Slovak Foreign 
Affairs Ministry</ORGANIZATION>, has handed a note to the <ORGANIZATION>Embassy</ORGANIZATION> of the 
Republic of <LOCATION>Hungary</LOCATION> in <LOCATION>Bratislava</LOCATION>. The note is a reaffirmation 
of <LOCATION>Slovakia</LOCATION>'s readiness to continue in talks on the temporary 
water economy regime on the <LOCATION>Danube</LOCATION> in connection with the 
