FT  26 OCT 92 / World News in Brief: Slovakia dams Danube
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<LOCATION>Slovakia</LOCATION> began damming the <LOCATION>Danube</LOCATION> to divert the river into the controversial
Gabcikovo hydroelectric barrage, sparking furious diplomatic protests from
neighbouring <LOCATION>Hungary</LOCATION>, which says the move is a territorial violation.
</TEXT>
